        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 1 at 10:16PM CDT until May 1 at 11:00PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northwestern Wheeler County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Northeastern Gray County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Southeastern Roberts County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Southwestern Hemphill County in the Panhandle of Texas...

* Until 1100 PM CDT.

* At 1015 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 17 miles northwest of Lora to 10 miles northwest of
Miami to near Codman to 9 miles northeast of Pampa, moving east at
35 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.

* Locations impacted include...
Codman, Canadian, Lora, Briscoe, and Miami.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
